rComments: Dispite the *not so bad* accent she is a very nice teacher. She is a very happy person and it rubs off. The class is hard unless you really know your music. Sections are hard too and the TA I had wasn't too helpful. The class has 1 midterm and 2 quizes before and after, there's lab midterms too so watch out.  I'd highly reccomend her

Overall, a good prof.  She's humorous, encourages participation, her english and accent is fine, although it may be hard to understand her explanations once in a while.  Always encourages students to go to her office hours or the TA's office hours if they need help.
